question: Jason places bananas on some baskets. Each basket can hold 23 bananas. If he has 344 bananas and 13 baskets, how many bananas won't he be able to place on the basket?
answer:
Jason will be able to place a total of 23*13 = <<23*13=299>>299 bananas.
Therefore, there are 344 - 299 = <<344-299=45>>45 bananas that he won't be able to place on the basket.
#### 45
